# Market Dragon — Domain & Invariants

Secure marketplace (Go) for trading/auctioning items in Aethoria. Full brief: `docs/IMPLEMENTATION_GUIDE.md`.

## Non-negotiables (guardian Vorynthax)
1. No invalid or **duplicate sale** of an asset (Legendary items are globally unique).
2. No Guild may commit beyond its **available funds** or **daily purchase cap**.
3. Stay **reliable + auditable** even when external services misbehave.
4. Must survive **duplicate operations**, **unreliable services**, and **concurrent requests**.

## Items
- **Common** / **Rare** → traded via **Limit Order** (fixed price, frozen once listed).
- **Legendary** → **Auction only**; exactly one copy exists, never reproduced.

## Wallet
- `Available Balance = Total Balance − Reserved Amount`.
- Every movement (**purchase / reserve / release**) MUST be recorded in a traceable ledger.

## Business rules (enforce all)
1. A Guild cannot bid on its own item.
2. A new bid must be **≥ 5% higher** than the current highest bid.
3. A bid may be cancelled **only if you are not the current highest bidder**.
4. Check balance (incl. reserves) before any financial commitment.
5. Each Legendary has **at most one active auction** at a time.

## Auction specifics
- Window default **24h** (configurable). Highest bid wins.
- Anti-snipe: a bid in the last **5 min** extends the auction by **5 min**.
- Placing a bid **reserves** funds (not debited); losing bids are **released immediately**.
- Auction ending with no bids → item becomes **Available** again.

## Oracle Price Service (external, must be mocked behind an interface)
- Pushes base prices ~every 30s; may be slow, wrong, or send zero/negative.
- Validate inputs, reject bad values, keep **last-known-good**; never corrupt state.
